# 🦀 Actix Web Auth API

A REST API built with Rust and Actix Web featuring JWT authentication and MongoDB integration.

## Tech Stack

- **Rust** — systems programming language
- **Actix Web** — fast async web framework
- **MongoDB** — NoSQL database
- **JWT (jsonwebtoken)** — authentication tokens
- **Serde** — JSON serialization/deserialization

## Features

- User registration with duplicate email check
- User login with JWT token generation
- Protected routes via JWT middleware
- View profile
- Update username and password
- Delete account

## Project Structure

```
src/
  main.rs       — server setup, routes, handlers, middleware
```

## API Endpoints

### Auth Routes (`/auth`)

| Method | Endpoint         | Description              | Auth Required |
|--------|------------------|--------------------------|---------------|
| POST   | /auth/register   | Register a new user      | ❌            |
| POST   | /auth/login      | Login and get JWT token  | ❌            |

### User Routes (`/user`)

| Method | Endpoint       | Description          | Auth Required |
|--------|----------------|----------------------|---------------|
| GET    | /user/profile  | Get current user     | ✅            |
| PUT    | /user/update   | Update user info     | ✅            |
| DELETE | /user/delete   | Delete account       | ✅            |

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Rust installed → [rustup.rs](https://rustup.rs)
- MongoDB running locally on port `27017`

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <your-repo>

# Run the server
cargo run
```

Server starts at `http://127.0.0.1:8080`

## Usage

### Register a new user

```bash
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "Arpit",
    "email": "arpit@example.com",
    "password": "123456"
  }'
```

### Login

```bash
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "email": "arpit@example.com",
    "password": "123456"
  }'
```

Response:
```json
{
  "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9....",
  "user_info": {
    "username": "Arpit",
    "email": "arpit@example.com"
  }
}
```

### Access protected route

```bash
curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/user/profile \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9...."
```

### Update user

```bash
curl -X PUT http://127.0.0.1:8080/user/update \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <your_token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "NewName",
    "password": "newpassword"
  }'
```

### Delete account

```bash
curl -X DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8080/user/delete \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <your_token>"
```

## How JWT Auth Works

```
POST /auth/login
        ↓
Server verifies credentials
        ↓
Server returns JWT token
        ↓
Client sends token in every request header
Authorization: Bearer <token>
        ↓
Middleware verifies token
        ↓
Valid → handler runs
Invalid → 401 Unauthorized
```

## Environment Variables

> ⚠️ Before deploying to production, move these to a `.env` file!

| Variable        | Current Value            | Description          |
|-----------------|--------------------------|----------------------|
| JWT_SECRET      | `change_in_production`   | Secret key for JWT   |
| MONGODB_URI     | `mongodb://localhost:27017` | MongoDB connection |

## Dependencies

```toml
[dependencies]
actix-web = "4"
mongodb = "3"
serde = { version = "1", features = ["derive"] }
serde_json = "1"
jsonwebtoken = "9"
futures = "0.3"
tokio = { version = "1", features = ["full"] }
```